{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χθιζ-ός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> (χθές) <b>of yesterday,</b> τὸ χ. χρεῖος their <b>yesterday's</b> debt, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.745 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ χ. πόνος <b>yesterday's</b> labour, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.126; ἡ χ. μέθη 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.13e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἱ χ. ἀβελτερίαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]75e,compare 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.40, etc.: frequently in adverbial sense, with Verbs, χθιζὸς ἔβη\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] he went <b>yesterday,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.424; χ. ἤλυθες 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.262; χ. ἐεικοστῷ φύγον ἤματι 6.170; ὅσσα.. χ. ὑπέσχετο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.141; χ. ἐμυθεόμην 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.451; ἴδον Μέντορα χ. 4.656 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; αἲ γάρ.. τοῖος ἐών τοι χ... ἐφεστάμεναι would I had stood by thee <b>yesterday!</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 24.379: _neuter_ χθιζόν as \">Refs</a>] <i>adverb</i>, ={χθές}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.195 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>neuter</i> <i>plural</i> χθιζά, see at {πρωιζός}.","strongNumber":"G9726","accentedUnicode":"χθιζός","shortDef":"of yesterday","mediumDef":"of yesterday","stepGloss":"of yesterday","stepTransliteration":"chthizos","_step_Type":"word"}]}